      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DOOR BUSTER (6) wasn't beaten far two back at Ascot in an Open 3YO race before jumping favourite in a CL1 last start and missing by 3.2L. Now lines up for the Peter Fernie barn in a Provincial assignment and carries less weight today. Nottle hops on board from a good draw and she can return to winning ways. CHIPILLY (4) couldn't bring up the hat-trick when beaten 1.3L in this grade last time out. She won well from the front here first-up at this trip and Fiore now takes the ride. Will be very tough to run down. THE SHOWVINIST (1) is third-up now and is a third-up winner in the past. He was steady to the line last start when 2.4L off the winner and drops right back in grade now. Won well at this track and trip fresh and can't be discounted. NATURAL GEM (3) has placed in both fresh efforts in the past and can be thereabouts on resumption. EEVALINA (2) trialled well coming in and is in the mix.",
